      "writtenOn": "2018-11-26T18:47:21Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "We should think about this carefully. If we\u0027ve already inserted the job into the DB, returning an error doesn\u0027t seem correct, because then we\u0027ll try to insert the same jobs again. My general feeling is that if there is an error in ModifiedJobs/ModifiedTasks, the resolution of the error is to reset all subscribers and have GetModified* return an error for existing subscribers.\n\nI\u0027m not completely sure how to do this for push notifications (i.e. PubSub), but one possibility is to send heartbeats, where the receiver resets itself if it misses 2 heartbeats. Another possibility is to add a UUID to messages where the receiver resets itself if the UUID changes between messages.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 176,
        "startChar": 3,
        "endLine": 176,
        "endChar": 13
      },
      "revId": "e7432b044c406b60b4c7e0b2a9131d0d82f1e000",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "5d49be0c_8efe1787",
        "filename": "task_scheduler/go/db/pubsub/modified.go",
